{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859918479,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797fd7270011T1x5bRhqlaWyA","messageID":"msg_d797fcb900016lUh0slllPBk4A","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ac6678cf9ca34126b0ecca5d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD Command Execution API (AR-015)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the command execution API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure and controlled command execution capabilities for sandboxed environments.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The PicoD command execution API provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Secure Command Execution**: Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments\n14: 2. **Resource Limits**: Enforce CPU, memory, and time limits on command execution\n15: 3. **Output Capture**: Capture stdout, stderr, and exit codes\n16: 4. **Streaming Support**: Optional streaming output for long-running commands\n17: 5. **Cancellation**: Support for command cancellation via context\n18: \n19: This implementation is the focus of AR-015 and builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in previous ARs.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/picod/picod.go` - Core PicoD structure and initialization\n28: - `pkg/picod/executor.go` - Command execution logic\n29: - `pkg/picod/limits.go` - Resource limit configuration and enforcement\n30: - `pkg/picod/output.go` - Output capture and streaming\n31: - `pkg/picod/security.go` - Security validations and sandboxing\n32: - Unit tests with mocked executors\n33: - Integration tests with real command execution\n34: \n35: ### Out of Scope\n36: \n37: - Container runtime integration (covered in separate ARs)\n38: - Network namespace manipulation\n39: - Filesystem isolation beyond chroot\n40: - User namespace management\n41: - Distributed command execution\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Impact Analysis\n46: \n47: ### Dependencies\n48: \n49: | Package | Purpose |\n50: |---------|---------|\n51: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n52: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n53: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n54: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n56: \n57: ### Affected Components\n58: \n59: 1. **Sandbox Manager**: Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n60: 2. **Workload Manager**: Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n61: 3. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n62: 4. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n63: \n64: ### Backward Compatibility\n65: \n66: - This is a new module with no existing API surface\n67: - No breaking changes to existing components\n68: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n69: \n70: ### Risk Assessment\n71: \n72: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n73: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n74: | Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n75: | Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n76: | Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n77: | Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n78: | Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Alternatives Considered\n83: \n84: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute)\n85: \n86: **Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n87: \n88: **Pros**:\n89: - Less code to maintain\n90: - Battle-tested implementations\n91: \n92: **Cons**:\n93: - May not meet specific security requirements\n94: - Additional dependency\n95: - Less control over resource limits\n96: \n97: **Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits.\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n100: \n101: **Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n102: \n103: **Pros**:\n104: - Simple implementation\n105: - Shell features available\n106: \n107: **Cons**:\n108: - Security risks (shell injection)\n109: - Harder to control resource limits\n110: - Additional attack surface\n111: \n112: **Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security.\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## Implementation Details\n117: \n118: ### PicoD Structure\n119: \n120: ```go\n121: type PicoD struct {\n122:     sandboxID     string\n123:     workDir       string\n124:     limits        *ResourceLimits\n125:     securityOpts  *SecurityOptions\n126:     logger        klog.Logger\n127: }\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### Resource Limits\n131: \n132: ```go\n133: type ResourceLimits struct {\n134:     Timeout       time.Duration\n135:     MaxCPU        float64\n136:     MaxMemory     int64\n137:     MaxOutputSize int64\n138:     MaxProcesses  int\n139: }\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Security Options\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: type SecurityOptions struct {\n146:     UID           int\n147:     GID           int\n148:     Capabilities  []string\n149:     ReadOnlyFS    bool\n150:     NoNetwork     bool\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Command Execution API\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: type Command struct {\n158:     Path    string\n159:     Args    []string\n160:     Env     []string\n161:     Dir     string\n162:     Stdin   io.Reader\n163:     Stdout  io.Writer\n164:     Stderr  io.Writer\n165: }\n166: \n167: type CommandResult struct {\n168:     ExitCode   int\n169:     Stdout     []byte\n170:     Stderr     []byte\n171:     Duration   time.Duration\n172:     OOMKilled  bool\n173:     Timeout    bool\n174: }\n175: \n176: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n177: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n178: func (p *Process) Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n179: func (p *Process) Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## Configuration Reference\n185: \n186: ### Environment Variables\n187: \n188: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n189: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n190: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n191: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n192: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n193: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## Testing Strategy\n198: \n199: ### Unit Tests\n200: \n201: 1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n202: 2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n203: 3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n204: 4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n205: 5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n206: 6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n207: \n208: ### Integration Tests\n209: \n210: 1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n211: 2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n212: 3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## Acceptance Criteria\n217: \n218: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n219: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory)\n220: - [ ] Output capture works correctly\n221: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n222: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n223: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n224: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n225: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n226: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## References\n231: \n232: - Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n233: - Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n234: - Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n\n(End of file - total 234 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD Command Execution API (AR-015)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the command execution API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure and controlled command execution capabilities for sandboxed environments.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe PicoD command execution API provides:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution**: Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments\n2. **Resource Limits**: Enforce CPU, memory, and time limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture**: Capture stdout, stderr, and exit codes\n4. **Streaming Support**: Optional streaming output for long-running commands\n5. **Cancellation**: Support for command cancellation via context\n\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-015 and builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in previous ARs.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775859918455,"end":1775859918477}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859918481,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797fe1d4001nco4j0P5JVUgnA","messageID":"msg_d797fcb900016lUh0slllPBk4A","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9ee1436c444c4c4d978958bd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ResourceLimits` struct in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n18:   - Fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64), `MaxOutputSize` (int64), `MaxProcesses` (int)\n19:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n20:   - Validation rules: Timeout > 0, MaxCPU >= 0, MaxMemory > 0, MaxOutputSize > 0, MaxProcesses > 0\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `DefaultResourceLimits()` function in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n23:   - Returns: Timeout=30s, MaxCPU=1.0, MaxMemory=128MiB, MaxOutputSize=10MiB, MaxProcesses=10\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SecurityOptions` struct in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n26:   - Fields: `UID` (int), `GID` (int), `Capabilities` ([]string), `ReadOnlyFS` (bool), `NoNetwork` (bool), `AllowedCommands` ([]string)\n27:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `DefaultSecurityOpts()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n30:   - Returns: UID/GID=-1 (no change), Capabilities=nil, ReadOnlyFS=false, NoNetwork=true, AllowedCommands=nil\n31: \n32: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define `Command` struct in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n33:   - Fields: `Path` (string), `Args` ([]string), `Env` ([]string), `Dir` (string), `Stdin` (io.Reader), `Stdout` (io.Writer), `Stderr` (io.Writer)\n34: \n35: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define `CommandResult` struct in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n36:   - Fields: `ExitCode` (int), `Stdout` ([]byte), `Stderr` ([]byte), `Duration` (time.Duration), `OOMKilled` (bool), `Timeout` (bool)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ExecutionErrorType` and error constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n39:   - Types: `ExecutionErrorTimeout`, `ExecutionErrorOOM`, `ExecutionErrorCancelled`, `ExecutionErrorSecurity`, `ExecutionErrorResource`, `ExecutionErrorExec`\n40: \n41: - [ ] **TASK-008**: Define `ExecutionError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n42:   - Fields: `Type` (ExecutionErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n43:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n44: \n45: ### Phase 2: PicoD Core Implementation\n46: \n47: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n48:   - Fields: `sandboxID` (string), `workDir` (string), `limits` (*ResourceLimits), `securityOpts` (*SecurityOptions), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `Option` type and functional options in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n51:   - Options: `WithWorkDir()`, `WithLimits()`, `WithSecurityOpts()`, `WithLogger()`\n52: \n53: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `New()` function in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n54:   - Creates PicoD with defaults, applies options\n55:   - Default workDir: `/tmp/picod/{sandboxID}`\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Config` struct and `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n58:   - Loads from environment variables: PICOD_WORKDIR, PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, PICOD_MAX_MEMORY, PICOD_MAX_CPU, PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE, PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES\n59:   - Applies defaults when env vars not set\n60: \n61: ### Phase 3: Command Execution\n62: \n63: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `Run()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n64:   - Flow: ValidateCommand → Create exec.Cmd → Apply resource limits → Capture output → Start → Wait → Build result\n65:   - Handle timeout, OOM, cancellation detection\n66:   - Return *CommandResult and error\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `Start()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n69:   - Starts command without waiting\n70:   - Returns *Process\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Define `Process` struct in `pkg/picod/process.go`\n73:   - Fields: `PID` (int), `cmd` (*exec.Cmd), `startTime` (time.Time)\n74:   - Methods: `Wait()`, `Kill()`, `Signal()`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Wait()` method for Process\n77:   - Waits for process completion\n78:   - Builds and returns CommandResult\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `Kill()` and `Signal()` methods for Process\n81:   - Sends signals to process\n82: \n83: ### Phase 4: Resource Limit Enforcement\n84: \n85: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `Apply()` method for ResourceLimits in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n86:   - Applies memory limits via syscall.Setrlimit (RLIMIT_AS)\n87:   - Applies process limits via syscall.Setrlimit (RLIMIT_NPROC)\n88:   - Configures cmd.SysProcAttr for process group\n89: \n90: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement CPU limit enforcement logic\n91:   - Use cgroups for CPU limits (Linux-specific)\n92:   - Fallback gracefully on non-Linux platforms\n93: \n94: ### Phase 5: Security Validation\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `ValidateCommand()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n97:   - Checks command against AllowedCommands allowlist\n98:   - Validates working directory is within workspace\n99:   - Checks for path traversal in arguments\n100:   - Validates environment variables (blocks LD_PRELOAD, LD_LIBRARY_PATH)\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `IsPathSafe()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n103:   - Checks if path is within allowed workspace using filepath.Abs and strings.HasPrefix\n104: \n105: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `DropPrivileges()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n106:   - Drops privileges to specified UID/GID using syscall.Setuid/Setgid\n107: \n108: ### Phase 6: Output Handling\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Define `OutputHandler` interface in `pkg/picod/output.go`\n111:   - Methods: `OnStdout([]byte)`, `OnStderr([]byte)`, `OnComplete(*CommandResult)`\n112: \n113: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `RunWithStreaming()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n114:   - Executes command with streaming output\n115:   - Calls handler callbacks as data becomes available\n116: \n117: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests\n118: \n119: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestResourceLimits_Validate` in `pkg/picod/limits_test.go`\n120:   - Valid limits → no error\n121:   - Timeout=0 → error\n122:   - MaxMemory<=0 → error\n123:   - MaxOutputSize<=0 → error\n124:   - MaxProcesses<=0 → error\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestSecurityOptions_Validate` in `pkg/picod/security_test.go`\n127:   - Valid options → no error\n128:   - Invalid UID/GID → error\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestPicoD_New` in `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n131:   - Default initialization\n132:   - WithWorkDir option\n133:   - WithLimits option\n134:   - WithSecurityOpts option\n135:   - WithLogger option\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Success` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n138:   - Execute simple command (echo)\n139:   - Verify ExitCode=0, Stdout captured\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n142:   - Command exceeds timeout\n143:   - Verify Timeout=true in result\n144:   - Verify ExecutionErrorTimeout returned\n145: \n146: - [ ] **TEST-006**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n147:   - Context cancelled before command completes\n148:   - Verify ExecutionErrorCancelled returned\n149: \n150: - [ ] **TEST-007**: Create `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n151:   - Capture stdout and stderr\n152:   - Verify correct output in CommandResult\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TEST-008**: Create `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n155:   - Command not in allowlist → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n156:   - Path traversal in args → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n157:   - Dangerous env var → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n158: \n159: - [ ] **TEST-009**: Create `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n160:   - Verify error type classification\n161:   - Verify Error() and Unwrap() work correctly\n162: \n163: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestProcess_Wait` in `pkg/picod/process_test.go`\n164:   - Start process, wait for completion\n165:   - Verify CommandResult built correctly\n166: \n167: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestProcess_Kill` in `pkg/picod/process_test.go`\n168:   - Start process, send kill signal\n169:   - Verify process terminated\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestLoadConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n172:   - Load from environment variables\n173:   - Verify defaults applied when env vars not set\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestIsPathSafe` in `pkg/picod/security_test.go`\n176:   - Safe paths → true\n177:   - Path traversal → false\n178:   - Absolute path outside workspace → false\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestRunWithStreaming` in `pkg/picod/output_test.go`\n181:   - Streaming output captured via handler\n182:   - Verify OnStdout/OnStderr/OnComplete called\n183: \n184: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n187:   - Full execution flow with real commands\n188:   - Verify end-to-end functionality\n189: \n190: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n191:   - Execute multiple commands concurrently\n192:   - Verify isolation and correct results\n193: \n194: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n195:   - Create memory-intensive command\n196:   - Verify OOM killed when exceeds limit\n197: \n198: - [ ] **TEST-023**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n199:   - Long-running command with streaming output\n200:   - Verify handler receives all output\n201: \n202: ### Phase 9: Documentation\n203: \n204: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types and functions\n205:   - Include usage examples in doc comments\n206: \n207: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Create `pkg/picod/README.md`\n208:   - Architecture overview\n209:   - Usage examples\n210:   - Configuration options\n211:   - Error handling guide\n212: \n213: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n214:   - Example: creating PicoD instance\n215:   - Example: running command\n216:   - Example: streaming output\n217: \n218: ## Acceptance Criteria\n219: \n220: - [ ] PicoD struct implements all required methods\n221: - [ ] Resource limits enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n222: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n223: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n224: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n225: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n226: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n227: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n228: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n229: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n230: - [ ] Error types properly classified and documented\n231: - [ ] Each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n232: \n233: ## Dependencies\n234: \n235: | Dependency | Status |\n236: |------------|--------|\n237: | Go 1.21+ | Required |\n238: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | Required |\n239: | context package | Required |\n240: | os/exec package | Required |\n241: | syscall package | Required |\n242: | AR-012 (Sandbox Infrastructure) | Completed |\n243: | AR-013 (Session Storage) | Completed |\n244: | AR-014 (Valkey Storage) | Completed |\n245: \n246: ## Test Infrastructure\n247: \n248: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `testEnv` struct for unit tests\n249:   - Mock logger\n250:   - Temporary test directories\n251: \n252: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Create mock OutputHandler for testing\n253:   - Track OnStdout/OnStderr/OnComplete calls\n254: \n255: ## Coverage Verification\n256: \n257: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n258:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n259:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n260:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n\n(End of file - total 260 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ResourceLimits` struct in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n  - Fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64), `MaxOutputSize` (int64), `MaxProcesses` (int)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Timeout > 0, MaxCPU >= 0, MaxMemory > 0, MaxOutputSize > 0, MaxProcesses > 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775859918462,"end":1775859918479}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859918485,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797fdcc4001SEF6fbbQgHhXwK","messageID":"msg_d797fcb900016lUh0slllPBk4A","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_487187fc8bbf4144a00339da","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 completed |\n12: \n13: This document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### Component Structure\n18: \n19: ```\n20: pkg/picod/\n21: ├── picod.go                 # Main PicoD struct and initialization\n22: ├── picod_test.go            # PicoD unit tests\n23: ├── executor.go              # Command execution logic\n24: ├── executor_test.go         # Execution unit tests\n25: ├── limits.go                # Resource limit definitions and enforcement\n26: ├── limits_test.go           # Resource limit tests\n27: ├── security.go              # Security validation and hardening\n28: ├── security_test.go         # Security tests\n29: ├── output.go                # Output capture and streaming\n30: ├── output_test.go           # Output handling tests\n31: ├── process.go               # Running process management\n32: ├── process_test.go          # Process management tests\n33: ├── errors.go                # Error type definitions\n34: └── config.go                # Configuration from environment\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Integration Points\n38: \n39: - **os/exec**: Standard library command execution primitives\n40: - **syscall**: Process management, signals, and resource limits\n41: - **context**: Command cancellation and timeouts\n42: - **k8s.io/klog/v2**: Structured logging\n43: - **pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1**: Type definitions for CodeInterpreter\n44: - **pkg/common/types**: SandboxInfo type definitions\n45: \n46: ### Execution Flow\n47: \n48: ```\n49: Client (WorkloadManager/CodeInterpreter)\n50:   ↓\n51: PicoD.New(sandboxID, options...)\n52:   ↓\n53: PicoD.Run(ctx, Command)\n54:   ├─ ValidateCommand(cmd, securityOpts)\n55:   ├─ ApplyResourceLimits(limits)\n56:   ├─ exec.CommandContext(ctx, path, args...)\n57:   ├─ Configure cmd.SysProcAttr\n58:   ├─ Start process\n59:   ├─ Monitor with timeout/limits\n60:   ├─ Capture stdout/stderr\n61:   └─ Return CommandResult\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Data Structures\n65: \n66: ### PicoD\n67: \n68: ```go\n69: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n70: type PicoD struct {\n71:     sandboxID    string\n72:     workDir      string\n73:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n74:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n75:     logger       klog.Logger\n76: }\n77: \n78: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n79: type Option func(*PicoD)\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### ResourceLimits\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n86: type ResourceLimits struct {\n87:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n88:     Timeout time.Duration\n89:     \n90:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n91:     MaxCPU float64\n92:     \n93:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n94:     MaxMemory int64\n95:     \n96:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n97:     MaxOutputSize int64\n98:     \n99:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n100:     MaxProcesses int\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### SecurityOptions\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n108: type SecurityOptions struct {\n109:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n110:     UID int\n111:     \n112:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n113:     GID int\n114:     \n115:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n116:     Capabilities []string\n117:     \n118:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n119:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n120:     \n121:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n122:     NoNetwork bool\n123:     \n124:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n125:     AllowedCommands []string\n126: }\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Command\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: // Command represents a command to execute\n133: type Command struct {\n134:     // Path is the command path\n135:     Path string\n136:     \n137:     // Args are the command arguments\n138:     Args []string\n139:     \n140:     // Env is the environment variables\n141:     Env []string\n142:     \n143:     // Dir is the working directory\n144:     Dir string\n145:     \n146:     // Stdin is the standard input\n147:     Stdin io.Reader\n148:     \n149:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n150:     Stdout io.Writer\n151:     \n152:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n153:     Stderr io.Writer\n154: }\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### CommandResult\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n161: type CommandResult struct {\n162:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n163:     ExitCode int\n164:     \n165:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n166:     Stdout []byte\n167:     \n168:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n169:     Stderr []byte\n170:     \n171:     // Duration is the execution duration\n172:     Duration time.Duration\n173:     \n174:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n175:     OOMKilled bool\n176:     \n177:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n178:     Timeout bool\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Process\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: // Process represents a running process\n186: type Process struct {\n187:     // PID is the process ID\n188:     PID int\n189:     \n190:     // cmd is the underlying exec.Cmd\n191:     cmd *exec.Cmd\n192:     \n193:     // startTime is when the process started\n194:     startTime time.Time\n195: }\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### OutputHandler\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n202: type OutputHandler interface {\n203:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n204:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n205:     \n206:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n207:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n208:     \n209:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n210:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n211: }\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ## API Contracts\n215: \n216: ### PicoD Initialization\n217: \n218: ```go\n219: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n220: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n221: \n222: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n223: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n224: \n225: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n226: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n227: \n228: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n229: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n230: \n231: // WithLogger sets the logger\n232: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ### Command Execution\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n239: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n240: \n241: // Start starts a command without waiting\n242: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n243: \n244: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n245: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ### Process Management\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: // Wait waits for the process to complete\n252: func (p *Process) Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n253: \n254: // Kill sends a signal to the process\n255: func (p *Process) Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n256: \n257: // Signal sends a specific signal to the process\n258: func (p *Process) Signal(sig syscall.Signal) error\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Resource Limits\n262: \n263: ```go\n264: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n265: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n266: \n267: // Validate validates resource limits\n268: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n269: \n270: // Apply applies resource limits to a process\n271: func (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### Security Validation\n275: \n276: ```go\n277: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n278: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n279: \n280: // Validate validates security options\n281: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n282: \n283: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n284: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n285: \n286: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n287: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n288: ```\n289: \n290: ### Configuration\n291: \n292: ```go\n293: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables\n294: func LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n295: \n296: // Config holds PicoD configuration\n297: type Config struct {\n298:     WorkDir         string\n299:     DefaultTimeout  time.Duration\n300:     MaxMemory       int64\n301:     MaxCPU          float64\n302:     MaxOutputSize   int64\n303:     MaxProcesses    int\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ## Error Handling\n308: \n309: ### ExecutionError\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n313: type ExecutionError struct {\n314:     // Type is the error type\n315:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n316:     \n317:     // Message is the error message\n318:     Message string\n319:     \n320:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n321:     Underlying error\n322: }\n323: \n324: // Error implements the error interface\n325: func (e *ExecutionError) Error() string\n326: \n327: // Unwrap returns the underlying error\n328: func (e *ExecutionError) Unwrap() error\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ### ExecutionErrorType\n332: \n333: ```go\n334: type ExecutionErrorType string\n335: \n336: const (\n337:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n338:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n339:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n340:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n341:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n342:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n343: )\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Error Conditions\n347: \n348: | Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n349: |-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n350: | Command exceeds timeout | `ExecutionErrorTimeout` | 408 Request Timeout | Command execution exceeded configured timeout |\n351: | Command exceeds memory | `ExecutionErrorOOM` | 413 Payload Too Large | Process was killed due to OOM |\n352: | Context cancelled | `ExecutionErrorCancelled` | 499 Client Closed Request | Client cancelled the operation |\n353: | Security violation | `ExecutionErrorSecurity` | 403 Forbidden | Command failed security validation |\n354: | Resource limit invalid | `ExecutionErrorResource` | 400 Bad Request | Invalid resource limit configuration |\n355: | Exec failure | `ExecutionErrorExec` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to start/execute command |\n356: \n357: ## Implementation Details\n358: \n359: ### PicoD Initialization\n360: \n361: ```go\n362: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD {\n363:     p := &PicoD{\n364:         sandboxID:    sandboxID,\n365:         workDir:      \"/tmp/picod/\" + sandboxID,\n366:         limits:       DefaultResourceLimits(),\n367:         securityOpts: DefaultSecurityOpts(),\n368:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n369:     }\n370:     \n371:     for _, opt := range opts {\n372:         opt(p)\n373:     }\n374:     \n375:     return p\n376: }\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### Command Execution Flow\n380: \n381: ```go\n382: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error) {\n383:     // 1. Validate command\n384:     if err := ValidateCommand(cmd, p.securityOpts); err != nil {\n385:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n386:             Type:    ExecutionErrorSecurity,\n387:             Message: \"command validation failed\",\n388:             Underlying: err,\n389:         }\n390:     }\n391:     \n392:     // 2. Create exec.Cmd\n393:     execCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, cmd.Path, cmd.Args...)\n394:     \n395:     // 3. Configure environment\n396:     execCmd.Env = cmd.Env\n397:     execCmd.Dir = cmd.Dir\n398:     \n399:     // 4. Apply resource limits\n400:     if err := p.limits.Apply(execCmd); err != nil {\n401:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n402:             Type:    ExecutionErrorResource,\n403:             Message: \"failed to apply resource limits\",\n404:             Underlying: err,\n405:         }\n406:     }\n407:     \n408:     // 5. Capture output\n409:     var stdoutBuf, stderrBuf bytes.Buffer\n410:     if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n411:         execCmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf\n412:     } else {\n413:         execCmd.Stdout = cmd.Stdout\n414:     }\n415:     if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n416:         execCmd.Stderr = &stderrBuf\n417:     } else {\n418:         execCmd.Stderr = cmd.Stderr\n419:     }\n420:     \n421:     // 6. Start execution\n422:     startTime := time.Now()\n423:     if err := execCmd.Start(); err != nil {\n424:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n425:             Type:    ExecutionErrorExec,\n426:             Message: \"failed to start command\",\n427:             Underlying: err,\n428:         }\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     // 7. Wait for completion\n432:     err := execCmd.Wait()\n433:     duration := time.Since(startTime)\n434:     \n435:     // 8. Build result\n436:     result := &CommandResult{\n437:         Duration: duration,\n438:     }\n439:     \n440:     if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n441:         result.Stdout = stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n442:     }\n443:     if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n444:         result.Stderr = stderrBuf.Bytes()\n445:     }\n446:     \n447:     // 9. Check for timeout/OOM\n448:     if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n449:         result.Timeout = true\n450:         err = &ExecutionError{\n451:             Type:    ExecutionErrorTimeout,\n452:             Message: \"command timed out\",\n453:         }\n454:     }\n455:     \n456:     if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n457:         if status, ok := exitErr.Sys().(syscall.WaitStatus); ok {\n458:             if status.Signal() == syscall.SIGKILL {\n459:                 result.OOMKilled = true\n460:                 err = &ExecutionError{\n461:                     Type:    ExecutionErrorOOM,\n462:                     Message: \"process killed due to OOM\",\n463:                 }\n464:             }\n465:         }\n466:         result.ExitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n467:     } else if err == nil {\n468:         result.ExitCode = 0\n469:     }\n470:     \n471:     return result, err\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Resource Limit Enforcement\n476: \n477: ```go\n478: func (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error {\n479:     if cmd.SysProcAttr == nil {\n480:         cmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{}\n481:     }\n482:     \n483:     // Set CPU limits via cgroups (Linux)\n484:     if l.MaxCPU > 0 {\n485:         // Use cpu.cfs_quota_us and cpu.cfs_period_us\n486:         // This requires cgroup setup\n487:     }\n488:     \n489:     // Set memory limits\n490:     if l.MaxMemory > 0 {\n491:         cmd.SysProcAttr.Setpgid = true\n492:         // Memory limits via setrlimit\n493:         syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_AS, &syscall.Rlimit{\n494:             Cur: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n495:             Max: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n496:         })\n497:     }\n498:     \n499:     // Set process limits\n500:     if l.MaxProcesses > 0 {\n501:         syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_NPROC, &syscall.Rlimit{\n502:             Cur: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n503:             Max: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n504:         })\n505:     }\n506:     \n507:     return nil\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### Security Validation\n512: \n513: ```go\n514: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error {\n515:     // 1. Check if command path is in allowlist\n516:     if len(opts.AllowedCommands) > 0 {\n517:         allowed := false\n518:         for _, allowedCmd := range opts.AllowedCommands {\n519:             if cmd.Path == allowedCmd {\n520:                 allowed = true\n521:                 break\n522:             }\n523:         }\n524:         if !allowed {\n525:             return fmt.Errorf(\"command %q not in allowlist\", cmd.Path)\n526:         }\n527:     }\n528:     \n529:     // 2. Validate working directory\n530:     if cmd.Dir != \"\" && !IsPathSafe(cmd.Dir, opts.WorkDir) {\n531:         return fmt.Errorf(\"working directory %q is outside workspace\", cmd.Dir)\n532:     }\n533:     \n534:     // 3. Check for path traversal in arguments\n535:     for _, arg := range cmd.Args {\n536:         if strings.Contains(arg, \"..\") {\n537:             return fmt.Errorf(\"argument %q contains path traversal\", arg)\n538:         }\n539:     }\n540:     \n541:     // 4. Validate environment variables\n542:     for _, env := range cmd.Env {\n543:         if strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_PRELOAD\") || strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_LIBRARY_PATH\") {\n544:             return fmt.Errorf(\"dangerous environment variable: %s\", env)\n545:         }\n546:     }\n547:     \n548:     return nil\n549: }\n550: \n551: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool {\n552:     absPath, err := filepath.Abs(path)\n553:     if err != nil {\n554:         return false\n555:     }\n556:     \n557:     absWorkDir, err := filepath.Abs(workDir)\n558:     if err != nil {\n559:         return false\n560:     }\n561:     \n562:     return strings.HasPrefix(absPath, absWorkDir)\n563: }\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ## Configuration\n567: \n568: ### Environment Variables\n569: \n570: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n571: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n572: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n573: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n574: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n575: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n576: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n577: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n578: \n579: ### Example Configuration\n580: \n581: ```go\n582: config := &Config{\n583:     WorkDir:        \"/tmp/picod\",\n584:     DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n585:     MaxMemory:      128 * 1024 * 1024, // 128 MiB\n586:     MaxCPU:         1.0,\n587:     MaxOutputSize:  10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10 MiB\n588:     MaxProcesses:   10,\n589: }\n590: ```\n591: \n592: ## Testing Strategy\n593: \n594: ### Unit Tests\n595: \n596: | Test | Purpose |\n597: |------|---------|\n598: | `TestPicoD_Run_Success` | Basic command execution |\n599: | `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` | Command exceeds timeout |\n600: | `TestPicoD_Run_OOM` | Command exceeds memory limit |\n601: | `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` | Context cancellation |\n602: | `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` | Stdout/stderr capture |\n603: | `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` | Invalid commands rejected |\n604: | `TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate` | Resource limit validation |\n605: | `TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate` | Security options validation |\n606: | `TestPicoD_WithOptions` | Functional options pattern |\n607: | `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` | Error type classification |\n608: \n609: ### Integration Tests\n610: \n611: | Test | Purpose |\n612: |------|---------|\n613: | `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full execution flow |\n614: | `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` | Multiple concurrent commands |\n615: | `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` | Verify limits are enforced |\n616: | `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` | Output streaming functionality |\n617: | `TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling` | Process signal handling |\n618: \n619: ### Test Fixtures\n620: \n621: ```go\n622: // mockOutputHandler implements OutputHandler for testing\n623: type mockOutputHandler struct {\n624:     stdoutCalls [][]byte\n625:     stderrCalls [][]byte\n626:     completeCalled bool\n627:     lastResult *CommandResult\n628: }\n629: \n630: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStdout(data []byte) {\n631:     m.stdoutCalls = append(m.stdoutCalls, data)\n632: }\n633: \n634: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStderr(data []byte) {\n635:     m.stderrCalls = append(m.stderrCalls, data)\n636: }\n637: \n638: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnComplete(result *CommandResult) {\n639:     m.completeCalled = true\n640:     m.lastResult = result\n641: }\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ## Acceptance Criteria\n645: \n646: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n647: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n648: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n649: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n650: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n651: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n652: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n653: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n654: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n655: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n656: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n657: \n658: ## Dependencies\n659: \n660: | Package | Purpose |\n661: |---------|---------|\n662: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n663: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n664: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n665: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n666: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n667: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n668: \n669: ## Affected Components\n670: \n671: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n672: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n673: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n674: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n675: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n676: \n677: ## References\n678: \n679: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n680: - AR-013: Session Storage\n681: - AR-014: Valkey Storage\n682: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n683: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n684: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n\n(End of file - total 684 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 completed |\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md","time":{"start":1775859918460,"end":1775859918482}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775859918513,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797fe695001uKqelB8C6uzTWl","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d797fcb900016lUh0slllPBk4A","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22465,"input":6,"output":290,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":2918,"read":19251}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775859921186,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797ff120001jI8Z9KOs447Xlm","messageID":"msg_d797fe6cb001yldg9IIWsW1Cup","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775859922958,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797ff3b2001eEVfm4kE0mjZmQ","messageID":"msg_d797fe6cb001yldg9IIWsW1Cup","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","type":"text","text":"Now I have a good understanding of the proposal format and the PicoD module context. Let me create the proposal for AR-016 - PicoD File Management API. Based on the spec, this is about file management operations within the PicoD sandbox environment.","time":{"start":1775859922957,"end":1775859922957}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859993697,"sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","part":{"id":"prt_d797ff80f001nEFEsTwUEMVDhE","messageID":"msg_d797fe6cb001yldg9IIWsW1Cup","sessionID":"ses_286806628ffe6mj9G5NkVzQbbv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_97a9be2200b84349bd2788f8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides:\n\n1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n\nThis implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `pkg/picod/filesystem.go` - File operations interface and implementation\n- `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go` - File metadata and information structures\n- `pkg/picod/quota.go` - Disk quota management and enforcement\n- `pkg/picod/path.go` - Path validation and normalization utilities\n- `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go` - File operation unit tests\n- `pkg/picod/quota_test.go` - Quota management tests\n- `pkg/picod/path_test.go` - Path validation tests\n- `pkg/picod/integration_test.go` - Integration tests (extended)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Network filesystem support (NFS, SMB, etc.)\n- File watching/notification systems\n- Advanced permissions (ACLs, extended attributes)\n- File encryption/decryption\n- Distributed file locking\n- Backup and snapshot functionality\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `os` | File operations and metadata |\n| `io` | Stream operations |\n| `io/fs` | Filesystem interfaces |\n| `path/filepath` | Path manipulation |\n| `context` | Operation cancellation and timeouts |\n| `syscall` | Low-level filesystem operations |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Existing PicoD types and limits |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Code Interpreter**: Will use file API for reading/writing code files and outputs\n2. **Agent Runtime**: Will use file API for accessing configuration and state files\n3. **Workload Manager**: Will use file API for managing job artifacts\n4. **Sandbox Manager**: Will configure filesystem quotas and permissions\n5. **Security Module**: Will validate file operation permissions\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new API surface within the existing PicoD module\n- No breaking changes to existing AR-015 command execution APIs\n- Extends PicoD struct with additional methods\n- Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Path traversal attack | Medium | Critical | Strict path validation, chroot-style isolation |\n| Disk space exhaustion | High | High | Enforce quotas, validate write sizes |\n| Symlink attacks | Medium | High | Resolve and validate symlink targets |\n| Race conditions | Medium | Medium | Atomic operations where possible, proper locking |\n| Information disclosure | Low | High | Validate read operations, enforce permissions |\n| Directory depth attacks | Low | Medium | Enforce maximum directory depth limits |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use os.* Directly\n\n**Approach**: Expose standard library `os` package functions directly\n\n**Pros**:\n- Minimal implementation effort\n- No additional abstraction layer\n- Full control for callers\n\n**Cons**:\n- No security enforcement\n- No quota management\n- Easy to misuse\n- Hard to audit file operations\n\n**Decision**: Wrap with security and quota validation layer.\n\n### Alternative 2: In-Memory Filesystem (afero)\n\n**Approach**: Use afero or similar in-memory filesystem abstraction\n\n**Pros**:\n- Easy testing and mocking\n- Built-in abstraction layer\n- Additional safety\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional dependency\n- Doesn't match real filesystem behavior exactly\n- May not support all operations needed\n\n**Decision**: Use real filesystem with validation for production accuracy.\n\n### Alternative 3: Container-mounted Volumes\n\n**Approach**: Delegate file operations to container runtime volume mounts\n\n**Pros**:\n- Leverages container isolation\n- No additional code to maintain\n- Clear security boundary\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires container runtime integration\n- Less flexible for non-container deployments\n- More complex orchestration\n\n**Decision**: Implement native file operations; container integration can be added later.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### File Quota\n\n```go\ntype FileQuota struct {\n    // MaxFileSize is the maximum size of a single file in bytes\n    MaxFileSize int64\n    \n    // MaxTotalSize is the maximum total size of all files in bytes\n    MaxTotalSize int64\n    \n    // MaxFiles is the maximum number of files allowed\n    MaxFiles int64\n    \n    // MaxDirectoryDepth is the maximum directory depth\n    MaxDirectoryDepth int\n}\n```\n\n### FileInfo\n\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    // Name is the file name\n    Name string\n    \n    // Path is the full path within the sandbox\n    Path string\n    \n    // Size is the file size in bytes\n    Size int64\n    \n    // Mode is the file mode and permissions\n    Mode os.FileMode\n    \n    // ModTime is the last modification time\n    ModTime time.Time\n    \n    // IsDir indicates if this is a directory\n    IsDir bool\n    \n    // FileType indicates the file type (regular, symlink, etc.)\n    FileType FileType\n}\n\ntype FileType string\n\nconst (\n    FileTypeRegular   FileType = \"regular\"\n    FileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n    FileTypeSymlink   FileType = \"symlink\"\n    FileTypeOther     FileType = \"other\"\n)\n```\n\n### File Operations Interface\n\n```go\ntype FileSystem interface {\n    // Read reads the entire contents of a file\n    Read(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)\n    \n    // ReadStream reads a file with streaming support\n    ReadStream(ctx context.Context, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    \n    // Write writes data to a file atomically\n    Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error\n    \n    // WriteStream writes from a stream with size limit\n    WriteStream(ctx context.Context, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error\n    \n    // Delete removes a file or empty directory\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n    \n    // DeleteAll removes a directory and all contents\n    DeleteAll(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n    \n    // Exists checks if a path exists\n    Exists(ctx context.Context, path string) (bool, error)\n    \n    // Info returns file metadata\n    Info(ctx context.Context, path string) (*FileInfo, error)\n    \n    // List lists directory contents\n    List(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)\n    \n    // Mkdir creates a directory\n    Mkdir(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error\n    \n    // MkdirAll creates a directory and all parent directories\n    MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, path string, perm os.FileMode) error\n    \n    // Rename renames/moves a file or directory\n    Rename(ctx context.Context, oldPath, newPath string) error\n    \n    // Copy copies a file\n    Copy(ctx context.Context, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    \n    // Quota returns current quota usage\n    Quota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Quota Usage\n\n```go\ntype QuotaUsage struct {\n    // UsedBytes is the total bytes used\n    UsedBytes int64\n    \n    // MaxBytes is the maximum bytes allowed\n    MaxBytes int64\n    \n    // FileCount is the number of files\n    FileCount int64\n    \n    // MaxFiles is the maximum files allowed\n    MaxFiles int64\n    \n    // PercentUsed is the percentage of quota used (0-100)\n    PercentUsed float64\n}\n```\n\n### PicoD Integration\n\n```go\n// PicoD struct extended with filesystem\ntype PicoD struct {\n    sandboxID    string\n    workDir      string\n    limits       *ResourceLimits\n    securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n    fileQuota    *FileQuota\n    logger       klog.Logger\n    \n    // File system operations\n    fs FileSystem\n}\n\n// FileSystem returns the file system interface\nfunc (p *PicoD) FileSystem() FileSystem\n\n// Convenience methods on PicoD\nfunc (p *PicoD) ReadFile(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]byte, error)\nfunc (p *PicoD) WriteFile(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error\nfunc (p *PicoD) ListDir(ctx context.Context, path string) ([]FileInfo, error)\nfunc (p *PicoD) DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, path string) error\nfunc (p *PicoD) GetQuota(ctx context.Context) (*QuotaUsage, error)\n```\n\n### Path Validation\n\n```go\n// ValidatePath validates a path is within the workspace\nfunc ValidatePath(path, workDir string) (string, error)\n\n// ResolvePath resolves a path to absolute, following symlinks\nfunc ResolvePath(path string) (string, error)\n\n// GetDepth returns the directory depth of a path\nfunc GetDepth(path string) int\n\n// IsWithinWorkspace checks if resolved path is within workspace\nfunc IsWithinWorkspace(path, workDir string) bool\n```\n\n### Atomic Write Implementation\n\n```go\n// Write atomically writes data to a file\nfunc (fs *fileSystem) Write(ctx context.Context, path string, data []byte) error {\n    // 1. Validate path\n    absPath, err := ValidatePath(path, fs.workDir)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Check quota\n    if int64(len(data)) > fs.quota.MaxFileSize {\n        return &FileError{\n            Type:    FileErrorQuotaExceeded,\n            Message: \"file size exceeds quota\",\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Write to temporary file\n    tmpPath := absPath + \".tmp.\" + uuid()\n    if err := os.WriteFile(tmpPath, data, 0644); err != nil {\n        return &FileError{\n            Type:    FileErrorWrite,\n            Message: \"failed to write file\",\n            Underlying: err,\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Atomic rename\n    if err := os.Rename(tmpPath, absPath); err != nil {\n        os.Remove(tmpPath) // Cleanup\n        return &FileError{\n            Type:    FileErrorWrite,\n            Message: \"failed to rename file\",\n            Underlying: err,\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILE_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Maximum single file size |\n| `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_TOTAL_SIZE` | No | `100MB` | Maximum total storage |\n| `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_FILES` | No | `1000` | Maximum number of files |\n| `PICOD_QUOTA_MAX_DEPTH` | No | `10` | Maximum directory depth |\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n\n### Example Configuration\n\n```go\nquota := &FileQuota{\n    MaxFileSize:       10 * 1024 * 1024,  // 10 MiB\n    MaxTotalSize:      100 * 1024 * 1024, // 100 MiB\n    MaxFiles:          1000,\n    MaxDirectoryDepth: 10,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `TestFileSystem_Read_Success` | Basic file read |\n| `TestFileSystem_Read_NotFound` | Read non-existent file |\n| `TestFileSystem_Read_PathTraversal` | Path traversal blocked |\n| `TestFileSystem_Write_Success` | Basic file write |\n| `TestFileSystem_Write_Atomic` | Atomic write verification |\n| `TestFileSystem_Write_QuotaExceeded` | Write exceeds quota |\n| `TestFileSystem_Delete_Success` | Delete file |\n| `TestFileSystem_Delete_All` | Delete directory recursively |\n| `TestFileSystem_Exists` | Check file existence |\n| `TestFileSystem_Info` | Get file metadata |\n| `TestFileSystem_List` | List directory contents |\n| `TestFileSystem_Mkdir` | Create directories |\n| `TestFileSystem_Rename` | Rename/move files |\n| `TestFileSystem_Copy` | Copy files |\n| `TestFileSystem_Quota` | Quota usage tracking |\n| `TestValidatePath_Success` | Valid paths accepted |\n| `TestValidatePath_PathTraversal` | Path traversal rejected |\n| `TestValidatePath_Symlink` | Symlink validation |\n| `TestGetDepth` | Directory depth calculation |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `TestFileSystem_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full file operation lifecycle |\n| `TestFileSystem_Integration_Concurrent` | Concurrent file operations |\n| `TestFileSystem_Integration_QuotaEnforcement` | Verify quotas are enforced |\n| `TestFileSystem_Integration_AtomicWrite` | Atomic write under load |\n| `TestFileSystem_Integration_LargeFiles` | Handle files near size limit |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\n// mockFileSystem creates a test file system\nfunc mockFileSystem(t *testing.T, quota *FileQuota) (FileSystem, func()) {\n    tmpDir := t.TempDir()\n    fs := NewFileSystem(tmpDir, quota, klog.Background())\n    cleanup := func() {}\n    return fs, cleanup\n}\n\n// createTestFile creates a test file with given size\nfunc createTestFile(fs FileSystem, path string, size int64) error {\n    data := make([]byte, size)\n    for i := range data {\n        data[i] = byte(i % 256)\n    }\n    return fs.Write(context.Background(), path, data)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `FileSystem` interface implements all required methods\n- [ ] Path validation prevents operations outside workspace\n- [ ] Quota enforcement works correctly (size, file count, depth)\n- [ ] Atomic writes prevent partial file corruption\n- [ ] Symlink attacks are prevented\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n- [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n- [ ] File operations are logged for audit trail\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### FileError\n\n```go\ntype FileError struct {\n    Type       FileErrorType\n    Message    string\n    Underlying error\n}\n\ntype FileErrorType string\n\nconst (\n    FileErrorNotFound      FileErrorType = \"not_found\"\n    FileErrorPermission    FileErrorType = \"permission\"\n    FileErrorQuotaExceeded FileErrorType = \"quota_exceeded\"\n    FileErrorPathTraversal FileErrorType = \"path_traversal\"\n    FileErrorWrite         FileErrorType = \"write\"\n    FileErrorRead          FileErrorType = \"read\"\n    FileErrorSymlink       FileErrorType = \"symlink\"\n    FileErrorDepth         FileErrorType = \"depth_exceeded\"\n)\n```\n\n### Error Conditions\n\n| Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n|-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n| File does not exist | `FileErrorNotFound` | 404 Not Found | Requested file was not found |\n| Path outside workspace | `FileErrorPathTraversal` | 403 Forbidden | Path validation failed |\n| Quota exceeded | `FileErrorQuotaExceeded` | 413 Payload Too Large | File/quota limit exceeded |\n| Permission denied | `FileErrorPermission` | 403 Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n| Symlink attack | `FileErrorSymlink` | 403 Forbidden | Symlink target outside workspace |\n| Directory depth exceeded | `FileErrorDepth` | 400 Bad Request | Path exceeds max depth |\n| Write failure | `FileErrorWrite` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to write file |\n| Read failure | `FileErrorRead` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to read file |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n- AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n- `pkg/picod/design.md`: PicoD Design Document\n- `pkg/picod/tasks.md`: PicoD Task List (AR-015)\n- `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775859993683,"end":1775859993693}}}}
